What are some adventurous water sports that can be enjoyed by a family of four, including children under the age of 12? Can you provide some Java code that demonstrates how to book these activities online?
Here is an example of how to book two recommended water sports, surfing and kayaking, using Java code:
public class WaterSportsBooking {
   public static void main(String[] args) {
      String[] participants = {"Parent", "Child1", "Child2", "Child3"};
      // Book surfing lessons for the family
      String surfingLessonUrl = "http://example.com/surfing-lessons";
      double surfingPrice = 75.00;
      int surfingNumParticipants = 4;
      if (participants.length == surfingNumParticipants) {
         // Book the surfing lessons online
         System.out.println("Booking surfing lessons for " + participants.length + " participants...");
         System.out.println("Total cost: $" + (surfingPrice * participants.length));
         System.out.println("Booking confirmation code: " + generateConfirmationCode());
      } else {
         System.out.println("Error: Number of participants for surfing lessons does not match the family size.");
      }
      // Book kayaking tour for the family
      String kayakingTourUrl = "http://example.com/kayaking-tour";
      double kayakingPrice = 110.00;
      int kayakingNumParticipants = 4;
      if (participants.length == kayakingNumParticipants) {
         // Book the kayaking tour online
         System.out.println("Booking kayaking tour for " + participants.length + " participants...");
         System.out.println("Total cost: $" + (kayakingPrice * participants.length));
         System.out.println("Booking confirmation code: " + generateConfirmationCode());
      } else {
         System.out.println("Error: Number of participants for kayaking tour does not match the family size.");
      }
   }
   public static String generateConfirmationCode() {
      // Generate a random alphanumeric confirmation code
      String alphanumeric = "0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz";
      StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
      for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
         int index = (int)(Math.random() * alphanumeric.length());
         sb.append(alphanumeric.charAt(index));
      }
      return sb.toString();
   }
}

For a family of four with children under the age of 12, there are several adventurous water sports that are both fun and safe. Here are some options:

1. **Snorkeling**: A great way for kids to explore underwater life in a safe environment.
2. **Stand-Up Paddleboarding (SUP)**: Suitable for calm waters, it's easy to learn and offers a great workout.
3. **Banana Boat Rides**: A thrilling and safe way for families to enjoy the water together.
4. **Rafting**: For a more adventurous experience, families can opt for family-friendly rafting trips.
5. **Canoeing**: Similar to kayaking, it can be a calm and educational experience on lakes or gentle rivers.

Below is a Java code snippet demonstrating how to book snorkeling and stand-up paddleboarding (SUP) activities online:

```java
public class WaterSportsBooking {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String[] participants = {"Parent", "Child1", "Child2", "Child3"};

        // Book snorkeling tour for the family
        String snorkelingTourUrl = "http://example.com/snorkeling-tour";
        double snorkelingPrice = 50.00;
        int snorkelingNumParticipants = 4;
        if (participants.length == snorkelingNumParticipants) {
            // Book the snorkeling tour online
            System.out.println("Booking snorkeling tour for " + participants.length + " participants...");
            System.out.println("Total cost: $" + (snorkelingPrice * participants.length));
            System.out.println("Booking confirmation code: " + generateConfirmationCode());
        } else {
            System.out.println("Error: Number of participants for snorkeling tour does not match the family size.");
        }

        // Book stand-up paddleboarding (SUP) session for the family
        String supSessionUrl = "http://example.com/sup-session";
        double supPrice = 60.00;
        int supNumParticipants = 4;
        if (participants.length == supNumParticipants) {
            // Book the SUP session online
            System.out.println("Booking SUP session for " + participants.length + " participants...");
            System.out.println("Total cost: $" + (supPrice * participants.length));
            System.out.println("Booking confirmation code: " + generateConfirmationCode());
        } else {
            System.out.println("Error: Number of participants for SUP session does not match the family size.");
        }
    }

    public static String generateConfirmationCode() {
        // Generate a random alphanumeric confirmation code
        String alphanumeric = "0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz";
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
            int index = (int)(Math.random() * alphanumeric.length());
            sb.append(alphanumeric.charAt(index));
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }
}
```

This code snippet includes booking logic for snorkeling and stand-up paddleboarding sessions. It checks the number of participants and calculates the total cost, providing a confirmation code for each booking. Adjust the URLs and prices to match the actual offerings of the service providers you choose.
